
** Install Trunk

Unpack the emacs-devel.tar.bz2 directory. Either do a "cvs update -kb"
of the emacs/nt directory or unix2dos tool.

  - mingw32-make

Install mingw32-make to c:/Programme/mingw and add the bin directory
to the cygwin path.

  - jpeg
  - png
  - zlib
  - tiff
  - xpm
  - gif

Install all the packages. Install too the xpm-src package and copy the
include file simx.h to $ROOT/include/X11.


"chmod u+w" of the following files:

  chmod u+w emacs/lisp/ps-print.el
  chmod u+w emacs/lisp/emacs-lisp/cl-loaddefs.el
  chmod u+w emacs/lisp/emulation/tpu-edt.el

configure with the following command:

  $ ./configure.bat --cflags -Ic:/Programme/GnuWin32/include

** Keys

  - (w32-register-hot-key [A-tab])

** Ispell

To get the ispell program for Windows see under

  ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/windows/emacs/contrib/ispell.zip 

Other goodies also in the contrib directory.

** TeX

If mictex is used then using the bash is maybe not good. Cygwin now
distributes too the teTex distribution.

** Fonts

See intlfonts in the nt-faq.

** Geometry

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\GNU\Emacs\Emacs.geometry

** BZR

  - bzr
  - python-crypto
  - python-paramiko

** W3M

  - Install in cygwin the w3m program. 
  - Download the Development version of emacs-w3m

  cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@cvs.namazu.org:/storage/cvsroot login
  cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@cvs.namazu.org:/storage/cvsroot co emacs-w3m
